        "body":  "﻿NEEDS_CORRECTION (doc-only).\n\nThe W08.2 code and test shape look correct, but the new module doc overclaims the parity relationship at `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/accelerator.rs:10-14`: it says the tests assert `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` and the menu resolver agree on **five** shared accelerators including Open. Ctrl+O is explicitly *not* an `EditorKeyCommand`; the test correctly asserts `from_key_press(KeyO, ctrl, false) == None` and then separately pins that the menu binds Ctrl+O to `Command::OpenFile` because the live path is the inline `window_event` arm.\n\nPlease reword that header to match the actual guard, e.g. \"the four `EditorKeyCommand` bindings agree with the menu, while Ctrl+O is separately pinned as the inline-open/menu OpenFile asymmetry; Ctrl+2/0/4 remain execution-only.\" The test body already has the right model; this is just the live doc surface.\n\nEverything else I checked is clear: two intended files only, `diff --check` clean, no Cargo/edge change, `keycode_to_shortcut` stays in editor-shell, live keyboard arms are untouched, and the intentional asymmetries are pinned rather than accidentally collapsed.\r\n",
