        "body":  "Fixed in `389e909` (comment-only).\n\nYou\u0027re right — the module header overstated the parity. `Ctrl+O` has no `EditorKeyCommand` bind (`from_key_press → None`); it routes via the inline `window_event` arm while the menu maps it to `OpenFile`, so Open is one of the pinned *asymmetries*, not an agreeing bind. The test already modelled this correctly.\n\nA stale-prose sweep of the file caught the **same overstatement in a second spot** — the parity test\u0027s lead comment (\"the five shared accelerators … resolve to the SAME logical command\"). Both corrected:\n\n- **Module header:** \"agree on the four `EditorKeyCommand`-routed shared accelerators (Save / Save-As / Undo / Redo)\"; `Ctrl+O` described as the inline-open / menu-`OpenFile` asymmetry alongside `Ctrl+2/0/4`.\n- **Parity test lead comment:** four binds resolve to the same command; `Ctrl+O` is a fifth shared bind pinned separately below as the intentional asymmetry.\n\nNo code/test/behaviour change. `fmt --check` clean; `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell accelerator` 4/4. CI re-running the full gate on `389e909`.\n",
