        "body":  "﻿APPROVED (content).\n\nRe-review of `389e909` clears the doc-only finding. The module header and the parity-test lead comment now say the four `EditorKeyCommand`-routed binds agree with the menu, while Ctrl+O is separately pinned as the inline-open/menu `OpenFile` asymmetry. A grep for the stale \"five shared / agree on five / Open-Save-...\" framing in `accelerator.rs` is clean.\n\nI also re-checked scope: exactly the intended two shell files, no Cargo/edge changes, `diff --check` clean, live keyboard arms untouched, `keycode_to_shortcut` stays shell-local, and the test pins both the shared binds and intentional asymmetries.\n\nCI is still finishing on this SHA (workspace tests + CodeQL Rust were in progress when checked), so this is content-approved with the usual CI + human-go hold.\r\n",
